```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "virenv_setup",
    "output_filename": "%x.out",
    "pi_group": "your_pi_group",
    "email_notification": "ALL",
    "email_address": "your_email",
    "partition": "standard",
    "cores": 1,
    "memory": "10gb",
    "time": "01:00:00",
    "modules": [
      "python/3.8/3.8.2",
      "cuda11/11.0",
      "cuda11-dnn/8.0.2",
      "cuda11-sdk/20.7"
    ],
    "python_version": "3.8",
    "packages": [
      "numpy==1.18.5",
      "scikit-learn==0.23.2",
      "torch==1.7.0+cu110",
      "torchvision==0.8.1+cu110",
      "torchaudio===0.7.0",
      "transformers==3.5.1"
    ]
  }
}
```

This script uses SLURM (Simple Linux Utility for Resource Management) to manage the execution of a job on a cluster. It requests resources like nodes, cores, memory, and time, and uses these resources to create a virtual environment for a Python project. 

The script uses several modules like Python 3.8, CUDA 11, and related libraries. It then installs specific versions of packages like NumPy, scikit-learn, PyTorch, and Hugging Face Transformers using pip.
